William R. Fatt – A Gem of Hotel Industry





William R. Fatt is the Chief Executive Officer and the Director of Fairmont, since October 1, 2001. In January 1998, William was appointed as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of FHR Holding INC., the position, he still presides. Up to October 1, 2001, William also served as the Executive Vice President of CPL. He is a Trustee and Vice Chairman of Legacy Hotels Real Estate Investment Trust. He also presides on the Director chair of Encana Corporation. Mr. William is also included in the Management Resources Compensation Committee and Risk Review Committee of Sun Life Financial Services of Canada. 
William R. Fatt served as Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of FHR Holdings Inc. (formerly, Canadian Pacific Hotels & Resorts Inc.) from January 1998 to October 2001 and Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Canadian Pacific Limited from January 1994 to December 1997. During the time span of August 1990 to January 1994, he served as Vice President of Finance & Accounting and Chief Financial Officer of Canadian Pacific Limited. From August 1988 to August 1990, Mr. Fatt served as a Vice President and Treasurer of Canadian Pacific Limited. He also worked as the Chief Executive Officer of Legacy Hotels Real Estate Investment Trust. Since June 1999, Mr. William has been the Vice Chairman of Legacy Hotels Real Estate Investment Trust. He also served as a Member of the Investment, Nominating, Compensation, Compliance and Governance Committees. Mr. William has also been the director of Enbridge Gas Distribution Inc. since 1998. Mr. Fatt also served as a Director of Doubletree Corp. and of its General Partner, Doubletree Partners, since December 1993. 
William R. Fatt obtained a Bachelor of Arts in Economics from York University. 
Fairmont Hotels and Resorts is one of the Canada based operators of a number of plush hotels and resorts across the globe. Lately, it is operating buildings across 18 countries, including Canada , the United States , Mexico , Bermuda , Barbados , Monaco , Germany , of Switzerland , Egypt , Kenya , United Kingdom , Tanzania , South Africa , the United Arab Emirates , Oman , Saudi Arabia , China and Singapore .
In Canada, the famous and legendary hotels of Fairmont are The Fairmont Empress in Victoria, BC, Hotel Vancouver in Vancouver, Fairmont Royal York in Toronto, the Château Frontenac in Quebec City or the Banff Springs Hotel in Banff, Alberta. 


 

 



